news.title: Mumbai: Bandra building to get notice for 'inoperative' fire-fight system
news.para: "The fire-fighting system was non-operational and we will issue a notice to the building. Our investigation is still on and the exact cause of the fire is not yet known," said Hemant Parab, the chief fire officer.

news.title: Nagpur: Six-storey flat scheme built in 2005, builder wants to add floor in 2022
news.para: Constructed in 2005, Poonam Pride Condominium in Pande Layout on Khamla Road has commercial shops on upper basement and ground floor and 18 flats on six floors.

news.title: Nashik civic body to seize ACs, TVs of property tax defaulters
news.para: The cash-strapped civic body has property tax dues of over Rs 175 crore. The idea of taking such action has come from NMC administrator Ramesh Pawar, who was previously posted in Mumbai where such a measure is in place.

news.title: Lucknow development body offers 5% discount to allottees hit by pandemic
news.para: Pawan Kumar Gangwar, secretary, LDA, said, “We have a scheme under which we offer 5% discount to those allottees who have cleared 75% of their payment against the plot, apartment or house within 60 days of the purchase.

news.title: Kanpur development body razes illegal colony in Bithoor
news.para: According to a KDA representative, KDA already launched a campaign against encroachments and illegal constructions. Several private developers are selling plots without getting clearance from KDA.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to hire private agencies to complete infra in nine colonies
news.para: The nine private colonies that have received approval for takeover by the MCG include Rosewood City, Greenwood City, Malibu Town, Ardee City, Sushant Lok-2 & 3, Mayfield Garden, Vipul Gardens and Uppal Southend.

news.title: Plot sales in Haryana get a push from Haryana government
news.para: Haryana government has allowed ground coverage of 75 per cent for residential plots up 250 sq m. The current ground coverage was 66 per cent.

news.title: NCLT admits plea against Modella Textile Industries
news.para: Interestingly, the company has argued that it has mortgaged several properties worth around ₹906 crore in favour of the financial creditor to secure loans allegedly payable against the debentures issued.

news.title: UltraTech secures legal view, set to bid for Ambuja, ACC
news.para: Since 2011, the Competition Commission of India has looked at 16 cement acquisitions, in eight of which it has given a "long form merger notifications"- a legalese for cases where the combined market share of the target and acquirer exceeds 15% market share in a relevant geographical market.

news.title: Property deeds for YEIDA areas to go online from June 1
news.para: The Yamuna Expressway Authority has implemented the citizen’s charter, under which 17 facilities related to the allottees would be available online. To start with, property transfer would be done online from June 1 for the residential category.

news.title: Haryana: Checks on brick kilns soon, those flouting norms to be closed
news.para: The direction comes days after a Supreme Court bench in April passed a slew of directions for the operation of brick kilns in NCR.

news.title: Asian Paints' profit at Rs 874 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Revenue from operations was up 20.60 per cent to Rs 7,889.94 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 6,541.94 crore in the corresponding period of previous fiscal year.

news.title: Kolhapur civic body offers 6% discount to property tax payers
news.para: The civic body has also managed to generate property tax bills for all property owners by Monday. Usually, the bills are generated by the end of May or in the first week of June. The dispatching of bills has also started.

news.title: Dalmia Bharat's profit down 6% to Rs 600 crore in Q4 FY22
news.para: Total expenses were at Rs 3,077 crore as against Rs 2,770 crore. However, revenue from operations was up 7.26 per cent to Rs 3,380 crore during the quarter under review as against Rs 3,151 crore in the same period a year ago.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body seals 314 buildings without BU permissions
news.para: In an affidavit, the AMC’s town development officer has stated that over the past one year the civic authorities have sealed 277 commercial and 37 residential buildings for want of BU permission.
